HEADWORD: Wiggery
<hw>Wig"ger*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A wig or
wigs; false hair.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>A.
Trollope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Any cover or screen, as red-tapism.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fire peels the <qex>wiggeries</qex> away from them [facts.]</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wiggle</ent>⟦br⟧
